enterVault(address,address,uint256,uint2.notice: Borrows a specified amount of fCash in the vault's borrow currency and deposits it all plus the depositAmountExternal into the vault to mint strategy tokens.

params.account: the address that will enter the vault
params.borrowAmount: amount to borrow, for fCash maturities this is the fCash amount. For pCash maturities this is the underlying borrowed.
params.depositAmountExternal: some amount of additional collateral in the borrowed currency to be transferred to vault
params.maxBorrowRate: maximum interest rate to borrow at, only applies as a slippage limit for fCash maturities
params.vaultData: additional data to pass to the vault contract

returns.vaultSharesAdded: the total vault shares tokens added to the maturity. Allows enterVault to be used by off-chain methods to get an accurate simulation of the strategy tokens minted.

exitVault(address,address,address,uint25.notice: Allows an account to withdraw their position from the vault at any time. Will redeem some number of vault shares to the borrow currency and close the borrow position by lending. Any shortfall in cash from lending will be transferred from the account, any excess profits will be transferred to the account.

params.account: the address that will exit the vault
params.exitVaultData: passed to the vault during exit
params.lendAmount: amount of fCash to lend if fixed, amount of underlying to lend if in pCash
params.minLendRate: the minimum rate to lend at
params.receiver: the address that will receive profits
params.vaultSharesToRedeem: amount of vault tokens to exit, only relevant when exiting pre-maturity

returns.underlyingToReceiver: amount of underlying tokens returned to the receiver on exit

rollVaultPosition(address,address,uint25.notice: Re-enters the vault at a different maturity. The account's existing borrow position will be closed and a new borrow position at the specified maturity will be opened. Strategy token holdings will transfer to the new maturity. Accounts can roll to longer or shorter dated maturities.

params.account: the address that will reenter the vault
params.depositAmountExternal: amount to deposit into the new maturity
params.maxBorrowRate: slippage protection for new borrow position
params.newBorrowAmount: amount of fCash to borrow in the next maturity

returns.vaultSharesAdded: the total strategy tokens added to the maturity, including any tokens rolled from the previous maturity. Allows rollVaultPosition to be used by off-chain methods to get an accurate simulation of the strategy tokens minted.

settleVaultAccount(address,address).notice: Settles a matured vault account by transforming it from an fCash maturity into a prime cash account. This method is not authenticated, anyone can settle a vault account without permission. Generally speaking, this action is economically equivalent no matter when it is called. In some edge conditions when the vault is holding prime cash, it is advantageous for the vault account to have this called sooner. All vault account actions will first settle the vault account before taking any further actions.

params.vault: the vault the account is in
